cheerfully. But after writing to The Times, challenging the anti-Tory views
of fellow scientists, he received several letters of support from
'distinguished science-policy people'.
Apart from Kealey, the only scientist that Conservative Central Office could
name as a defender of government policy is Philip Treleaven, professor of
computing at London University. He is also the Tory candidate in the London
constituency of Southall.
