domestic and US sales.
It also lowered its forecast for parent net profits to Y500m in 1991-92,
from a December forecast of Y7bn, against losses of Y66.46bn in 1990-91. The
downward revision was based on an appraisal of its securities losses, it
said.
It lowered its forecast of parent sales slightly.
