</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
CUMMINS Engine, the US diesel engine manufacturer, said it expected to
report a profit for the first quarter, AP-DJ reports.
The company posted net income of Dollars 17.2m, or Dollars 1.02 a share, in
the same period a year earlier, after a big gain from an accounting change.
Without the gain, Cummins would have posted a loss of Dollars 34.3m, or
Dollars 2.44, for the period.
Cummins added that it expected second-quarter profits to exceed those of the
first quarter, assuming there was 'no deterioration in business conditions'.
In last year's second quarter, Cummins posted a loss of Dollars 17.2m, or
Dollars 1.29.
Mr James Henderson, president and chief operating officer, said 1991 had
been a year of 'significant progress' for the company, in spite of recession
in most of its world markets.
Mid-range engine volume increased 6,000 units over 1990 levels, while
heavy-duty engine volume dropped by about 18,000 units.
