FT  08 APR 92 / Election 1992: FT election share index
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
THE PREVAILING trend of the campaign was again visible yesterday as shares
that might benefit from a Labour win outperformed those that might gain from
a Conservative victory.
Since the campaign started, 'Tory gainers' have dropped more than 12 per
cent - twice the fall in the FT-SE index of big-company shares. 'Labour
gainers' have fallen less than 4 per cent.
The index sections reflect views of which companies stand to gain and lose
most from the result.
