<TEXT>
AN OPINION poll last night suggested that Mr Michael Forsyth, the
controversial Scottish Office minister, is likely to lose his seat in
Stirling, where he had a majority of 548 in 1987.
According to a System 3 survey for The Herald newspaper and Scottish
Television, Labour candidate Ms Kate Phillips is on 40 per cent (against 36
