FT  08 APR 92 / Election 1992: Christian Democrats accept Tory MEPs
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
BRITAIN'S 32 Conservative Euro MPs were last night accepted into the
European parliament's Christian Democrat group - which favours proportional
representation.
Their application to join was accepted by the Christian Democrats with a
sizeable majority - 66 in favour and 28 against, with five abstentions.
Dutch Christian Democrat Mr Tom Penders, who opposed having the Tories as
allied members, said afterwards: 'That's it. They are de facto inside the
group, and have accepted all the principles we stand for.'
The move came amid reports that Mr John Major had signalled his willingness
to consider accepting PR for elections to the European parliament in 1994.
