investments in North Sea oil and gas activities, in which it is in
partnership with Texaco and Shell in Danish Underground Consortium, was
DKr1.4bn.
An increase in the dividend in the twin parent companies which control the
group was proposed. The dividend in D/S 1912 will go up from 40 to 45 per
cent to DKr97m and in D/S Svendborg from 40 to 60 per cent to DKr89m.
Oil and gas activities, which comprise production from the Danish sector of
the North Sea, gave an increase in operating profits to DKr1.47bn from
DKr1.14bn, but net profits, after inter-group allocations and tax, were down
to DKr113m from DKr126m.
Results by the Maersk Line container fleet and the tanker fleet were better
than in 1990, said the statement, while bulk carriers and gas tankers did
slightly less well and the offshore rigs and supply vessels yielded
unchanged results.
Shipping results in 1992 are likely to be 'significantly below' 1991.
